cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE

This paper focuses on the security and fraud detection in the EOSIO blockchain and its associated DApps. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves large-scale data analysis and measurement study, which suggests the possibility of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of the EOSIO blockchain and its ecosystem, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
